{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place milk, cream, sugar, egg yolks, rum, vanilla, cinnamon sticks and nutmeg in mixing bowl then cook <b>8 min\/80°C\/\/speed 4<b>.","Place ice cubes in a large bowl, then rest another large bowl over it. Discard cinnamon then pour mixture through a sieve into the top bowl to cool rapidly, whisking gently for 2 minutes.","Leave mixture in bowl over ice cubes until cool. Cover with cling film, pressed to the surface, then place in fridge until cold.","Pour mixture into a shallow freezer-proof container, cover tightly with lid or cling film then freeze for at least 10 hours.","Before serving, place frozen mixture in fridge for 15-20 minutes to soften, then place a large bowl in freezer. Once mixture has softened, cut into pieces (4 cm x 4 cm) with a sharp knife.","Place half ice cream cubes in mixing bowl and crush <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>, then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>, with aid of spatula.","Remove bowl from freezer. Transfer ice cream mixture to bowl, then repeat process with remaining ice cubes. Place ice cream in freezer for 10-15 minutes before serving.","Serve eggnog ice cream garnished with freshly grated nutmeg."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["370 g whole milk","350 g double cream","70 g caster sugar","6 egg yolks, from medium eggs","1 tsp vanilla bean paste","3 Tbsp dark rum","2 cinnamon sticks, broken in pieces","¼ tsp ground nutmeg","ice cubes, for cooling","whole nutmeg, grated, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r248409","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-h4pUYJeSPyI\/XZWeiBxH5iI\/AAAAAAAAe1o\/ZDO-euPCHKw4Zmwp7TY1e2hV8PRovjqMwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_b8uyHe2c845DVBiZ.png","title":"Eggnog Ice Cream","publishedAt":"2017-12-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"20 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"13 g","calories":"1096 kJ \/ 262 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sieve, large bowl, cling film, sharp knife, wire whisk, shallow freezer-proof container, fridge, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["Enjoy 